OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FPrepare yourselves for another invented
OL,7,Frow over a supposed BBC controversy.
OL,9,FEarlier this month, the BBC finally
OL,10,Fprovided some clarity about the future
OL,11,Fof Radio 4 Long Wave.
OL,13,FIt will be closed later this year.
OL,15,FAt least 2 months' notice will be
OL,16,Fprovided and there will be support for
OL,17,Fthe vulnerable ` as there should be.
OL,19,FI think we can all imagine the
OL,20,Fheadlines in the Mail, Express and
OL,21,FTelegraph when the exact date is
OL,22,Fannounced.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14102
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FJust think for a moment how unlikely it
OL,7,Fis that someone will lose access to
OL,8,FRadio 4 after the switch off.
OL,10,FBy my reckoning this would mean:
OL,12,F- They had no access to FM radio. It's
OL,13,Fbeen impossible to buy a decent radio
OL,14,Fsince the late 1980s which does not
OL,15,Fhave FM. There are few areas where
OL,16,Fanyone actually lives which do not have
OL,17,Facceptable FM reception.
OL,19,F- No access to DAB digital radio. The
OL,20,Fcoverage of the BBC's national
OL,21,Fmultiplex matches the coverage of BBC
OL,22,FFM radio.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14103
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,F- No TV. Freeview, Freesat and Sky all
OL,7,Fcarry Radio 4.
OL,9,F- No internet access.
OL,11,FIn other words, the individual must be
OL,12,Feither extremely vulnerable or have
OL,13,Fwilfully excluded themselves from a lot
OL,14,Fof the modern world.
OL,16,FOf course, there will be a few with a
OL,17,Fdifferent story.
OL,19,FThe person who drives their car through
OL,20,Fa remote area who finds FM or DAB
OL,21,Funreliable or the person who cherishes
OL,22,Fa beautiful old radio.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14104
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FWhile their concerns cannot be
OL,7,Fdismissed out of hand, it would still
OL,8,Fbe hard to justify keeping an obsolete
OL,9,Ftechnology going for their benefit.
OL,11,FIf you have an elderly or vulnerable
OL,12,Ffriend who still listens to AM radio,
OL,13,Fnow is the time to give them help.
OL,14,FTreat them to a new radio and show them
OL,15,Fhow to use it.
OL,17,FBut we can all imagine the headlines
OL,18,Fahead.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14105
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FThere will be claims the BBC is
OL,7,Fabandoning its heritage, abandoning the
OL,8,Felderly, abandoning the vulnerable. Get
OL,9,Fyour bingo cards prepared now.
OL,11,FAnd for the star prize, just wait for
OL,12,Fthe claim that the captain of a
OL,13,Fsubmarine will fire off the nuclear
OL,14,Fmissiles because they can't hear The
OL,15,FArchers or Woman's Hour.
OL,17,FThere are many horrible decisions
OL,18,Ffacing the BBC. It recently warned of
OL,19,F2,000 job losses.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14106
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FThose of us who genuinely care about
OL,7,Fthe BBC could well be fighting cuts
OL,8,Fwhich nobody wants to make.
OL,10,FAnd no doubt there will be tough
OL,11,Fchoices about programmes and services.
OL,12,FCBBC and BBC Four as linear channels
OL,13,Fhave been on borrowed time for years.
OL,15,FBut I'm afraid a fight to keep Radio 4
OL,16,Fon long wave is not a fight worth
OL,17,Fhaving.
OL,19,FThe closure of the service will be an
OL,20,Fimportant milestone in broadcasting
OL,21,Fhistory and should be appropriately
OL,22,Fmarked.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,142,140,200,120,0,100
PN,14107
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F141A1777206670
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/7
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCClosure of Radio 4 LW is the
OL,4,Cright decision
OL,5,
OL,6,FBut beware those false friends who will
OL,7,Fbe only too keen to exploit a decision
OL,8,Fwhich some, for genuine reasons of
OL,9,Fsentiment or nostalgia, will not like.
OL,23,EPub: 26-Apr-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
